name: The Maltese
directions: Turn right when you walk through the door and head straight back.
comment: This is a bar. It may not be a good option if you are a recovering addict.

name: The Good Will Social Club
directions: Back of the area with the long table, past pinball machines
comment: It's safe space that promotes inclusivity and respect. They will have no problem with someone seeking refuge and a safe place to use the bathroom in their facility

name: Hillman Library
directions: Ground floor near back left
comment: Open to public. Typically opens at 10 a.m. Sunday, 24 hours Monday-Thursday, Open until 10 p.m. Friday, Open 9 a.m. to 10 p.m. on Saturday, but varies for holidays and Summer.

name: Moe's Southwest Grill
directions: In the back
comment: For customers only, but menu items are inexpensive. There are two gendered single occupancy accessible bathrooms. People often use the "wrong" bathroom when theirs is busy and no one fusses about it

name: butte college main campus
comment: I know there are two gender-neutral restrooms on campus, last I checked. can't say much about them as I never used them.

name: Benedum Hall
directions: Ground floor back hallway on North Bouquet Street side
comment: Building normally unlocked to public

name: UWS Student Union
directions: as you enter, go straight past the reception desk and then to the left
comment: if there are staff at reception you will probably need to show UWS student id, if staff aren't there you should be fine to go straight inside

name: Nor Lea Hospital
directions: Go in through old clinic pass the reception to the right. Unisex bathroom is across from men's restroom.

name: Sperry Park
directions: In spring and summer time, there are two portajohns available.
comment: It's outdoors, at a baseball field. There are two, one towards the snack shack, and the other near the handicap parking spaces.

name: Plan B Burger Bar
comment: you might have to get a burger, fries, or bourbon, but it'll be delicious.  gf/veg options too, and I've always been treated just like any other customer.

name: Psychedelicatessen
directions: In the back at the end of the counter. Door says "yup".

name: Target
directions:
First floor, sharply to the left after you walk in the doors, before customer service. Turn all the way left, further toward the front of the building than the other restrooms, to find the all-gender restroom. 

Inmediatamente despues entrando las puertas, vuelte a la isquierda. El ba単o para todos esta a la isquierda de los otros ba単os.
comment:
It is one large all-gender bathroom that is wheelchair accessible and has a changing table. 
Es un ba単o singular con mesita para cambiar los pa単ales, y hay espacio para una silla con ruedas.

name: Ka Prow
comment: Restaurant

name: Stone Path Massage and Energy Center
directions: Straight back and to the left.
comment: All are welcome, private bathroom.

name: Diamond Green
directions: Get key from front desk and it's thru the hallway
comment: Just walk in and ask for the bathroom key

name: Seattle University Lemieux Library
directions: 3rd floor across from the Circulation Desk
comment: Private college but the library is open to the public

name: Flowerland Nursery & Store
directions: outside on thr back of the main store building, can be tricky to find but staff is veey helpful and can point the way

name: Slackwater Pizzaria
directions: To the right of the bar.

name: Rustic Theatre
directions: Single stall locking restroom.
comment: You must pay for something.

name: MECCA Materials Exchange Center for Community Arts
Wander Brewing
directions: Towards the back of the building, closer to the brewing tanks than the bar. There are 2.

name: Pine Street Barber Shop
directions: All the way back, last door on the right
comment: If you aren't here for a hair service please just say hi and ask to use the restroom. We will never say no, we just want to be aware of what you are doing.

name: First Unitarian Universalist Church
directions: Enter and turn left to go down steps/ramp and through the hall at the back on the left. Two single person stalls are on the left side past the mini library. First is a women's, second is gender inclusive.
comment: You don't have to be a member, but the door is primarily unlocked when the building is occupied. Come say hi!

name: The Rendezvous
directions: Two all gender single stalls in the back of the restroom

name: Berlyn
directions: To the right, across from the bar.

name: Ccit building
directions: One on both first and second floor

name: Ccit building
directions: One on both first and second floor

name: Twiggs Coffee
directions: To the rear and the left of the coffee shop, first door on the right in the little hall way. There's another Unisex restroom down the hall a bit and also to the right. Use the first one if possible. The second one technically belongs to the small meeting hall next door.
comment: Buy a cup of coffee if you can! This is a great little coffee shop, and a local cornerstone.

name: Stones Throw Brewery
directions: In the backyard of the brewery. There are two.
comment: You probably could use it without buying anything but it's definitely not a bad place to grab a beer afterwards.

name: Northeastern University Curry Student Center
directions: fourth floor, there is an elevator but it is "at the end of the hall" depending on where you answer.
comment: Not open 24/7, but pretty late, and it's a building that constantly has non-university affiliated people in it unlike some of the other northeastern buildings.

name: The Shedd Institute Community Music School
directions: Second and third floor just off the elevator

name: University of Michigan Flint
directions: On every floor there are single stall, gender neutral bathrooms.

name: University of Mary Washington University Center
directions: Second floor in the back, on the right.

name: Collis Center
directions: First floor

name: Butter Bakery Cafe
directions: about halfway back on the left

name: Hy-Vee
directions: There is a one occupancy bathroom near the pharmacy up front in this Hy-Vee.

name: Publix
comment: Family restroom at the front of the store

name: Lucie Monroe's Coffee Company
directions: As you enter, there is a hallway ahead of you and a bit to the right that contains two single-occupancy bathrooms with gendered signage.

name: Paul
directions: When you enter, turn left and go up the ramp to the seating area and then to the back.
comment: Two unisex single-stall bathrooms.

name: Blockbuster Video
comment: You do have to ask for an employee to unlock it, and I would browse around and/or buy something too!

name: J. Crew Mercantile
directions: In Plymouth Meeting mall (storefront is on the outside of the mall) a few stores to the left of Whole Foods. Bathrooms are in the hallway in the back right.
comment: Single stall men's and women's bathrooms. There's no requirement to be a customer so don't worry if you need an employee to unlock it.

name: Cedar Rose Park
directions: Public bathroom at the park, just outside the fenced play area
comment: No closing door - uses a chain to indicate someone is there, walk around corner to the toilet.

name: Harvest Brewing
directions: Single bathroom for anyone's use

name: Cheesie's Pub and Grub
directions: Back right corner of store.
comment: Two single stalled, gender neutral restrooms, LGBTQ friendly restaurant.

name: McDaniel College
directions: First floor of Hoover library, basement of Hill hall,
comment: The buildings close at midnight.

name: Pisces Pet Emporium
directions: Back left of fish area
comment: Have to ask for key at customer service

name: Cedar Rose Park
directions: Public restroom at the park, just outside the fenced play area

name: Roanoke County Public Library - Vinton Branch
directions: There are two single-occupancy bathrooms with gendered signage in the second floor hallway.

name: Cedar Rose Park
directions: Public restroom at the park, just outside the fenced play area

name: Twisted Branch Tea Bazaar
directions: On the Downtown Mall, an upstairs business next to Miso Sweet and across from the Nook. It has two bathrooms marked WC 1 and WC 2 (Water Closet, an old term for bathrooms) in the hallway towards the back of the business.

name: Starbucks
directions: You'll notice the restroom to the left as soon as you walk in.

name: Starbucks
directions: You'll notice the gender neutral restroom to the left as soon as you walk in

name: Starbucks
directions: You'll notice the gender neutral restroom to the left as soon as you walk in

name: Eastern Cafe
directions: Second floor, in the back.
comment: Technically paying customers only but you don't need a key.

name: Wilkinson Hall
directions: Walk up the stairs into the side entrance and it's to your left, a bit under the stairs.
comment: Act like you're a student or visitor of Chapman University- it's an open campus.

name: Piato's
comment: Single stall bathrooms

name: North Morlan Hall
directions: Bottom floor of North Morlan Hall, next to the lounge and trash room.
comment: You have to be a resident or visitor of Chapman University.

name: Lawton's Pharmacy
comment: This bathroom is locked. I usually ask for the key and they'll let me in.

name: Townhouse Cocktail Lounge
directions: In the back by the jukebox
comment: For customers only. Two single stall, single gender restrooms, but they really don't care which one you use. Lots of drag queen and genderqueer customers

name: Tim Hortons
comment: Single toilet gendered washrooms

name: Kum & Go
directions: Back of store by cooler
comment: Open to all. Friendly cashiers. Very safe store.

name: Spectrum 8
directions: By theatres 1 & 2 which is to the left of the snack bar.
comment: You generally have to be a paying customer but if you ask nicely when it isnt busy people will usually let you use the bathroom.

name: Science Building
directions: On the first floor, down the hall from the Jumping Bean
comment: This is a single stall "female" washroom.

name: Discover Teas
directions: Back of the store, first door on the left through the bunny curtain
comment: Encouraged to be a paying customer; they usually have a free sample of tea for you to try. Staff is extremely friendly and trans-positive, if you can't afford anything but just need a place to be for a few minutes, they will help you out if they can!

name: Avalon Mall
directions: Two family/unisex washrooms. One to the left of the foodcourt entrance and one down the hallway next to Aldo Shoes.
comment: The family/unisex bathroom next to Aldo is less busy.

name: Milagros Latin Kitchen
directions: Straight back from front door and can also access from bar area.
comment: Milagros got it right! They just remodeled their restrooms from one rest room per sex to four fully enclosed "water closets". Walk back out to the common area for wash basins which is also setup as a safe zone. Show them so love!

name: Memorial University Student Centre
directions: Sixth floor. Accessible by elevator!
comment: MUN Sexual and Gender Advocacy Centre is on the same floor. A great place to stop in for support or a chat!

name: Stow-Munroe Falls Public Library
directions: Located on second floor next to other restrooms. Take elevator or stairs up and follow the restroom signs.
comment: Private/Single stall restroom is labeled Family Restroom but is open for any use.

name: Parchment Coffee
directions: In back
comment:
Restroom is near counter, and you may be expected to make a purchase.

Note: Some regulars, and at least one barista, were vocal Trump supporters during the campaign. Don't know if that's still the case; may or may not be a friendly environment.

name: Cacciatori's
directions: In the back left of restaurant

name: Samek Art Museum
directions: 3rd floor down the back entrance hall from the museum.
comment: Bucknell LGBTQ resource center is down the hall

name: Esso Gas Station
directions: far end of first floor, by the door with a ramp

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: Towards the back of the store, past the hot bar
comment: Team members are almost always LGBT+ friendly. It's okay to ask for help if you need it.

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: Towards the back of the store, past the hot bar
comment: Team members are almost always LGBT+ friendly. It's okay to all for help if you need it.

name: Fresh Brothers
directions: Walk straight back from the entrance.

name: Sashimi Express
comment: Pretty sure you have to be a paying customer, but the food is good, so there's that.

name: Java Roaster
directions: Straight back, first door.

name: New Orleans Public Library - Norman Mayer Branch
directions: Second floor restroom is unisex, but ask for key at reference desk.

name: Java Roaster
directions: Straight back, first door

name: New Orleans Public Library - Milton H Latter Branch
directions: First floor to the right of the circulation desk.
